{
  "text": "In this paper, we proposed a deep learning architecture that uses CNN together with time-domain statistical features and demonstrated its capability to produce an effective position-independent HAR. In addition, we applied the proposed architecture to the position detection problem. We noticed that the proposed model revealed excellent results compared to the state-of-the-art method presented in [CITATION_1] . These results support claims that deep learning approaches are more generic and robust than other traditional machine learning methods.",
